      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MANSON LAMPS (1) shapes nicely here coming off a superb 30.08 victory at Wagga over 525m. Hard to top on the time from last start. SUPER SASSY (3) doesn't have the best strike-rate. Finished in the minors latest when second (29.84) at this track and may be close to breaking through. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and two minor placings to her credit. Hard to beat again. WOOLGOOLGA (8) has been in the placings at his last two runs, most recently when third (29.87) in a Grade 5 over 520m at this track. Well placed here and can atone this time. ANCIENT EGYPTIAN (2) collected a minor prize last start and ran time in the process - must be considered.",
